com.innowhere.jnieasy.core.typedec
Interface NativeInstanceMethodSignature

All Superinterfaces:
NativeBehaviorSignature, NativeMethodSignature
public interface NativeInstanceMethodSignature
extends NativeMethodSignature

The NativeInstanceMethodSignature interface represents the native signature declaration of native instance methods.

Author:
Jose M. Arranz Santamaria
See Also:
NativeSignatureManager.decInstanceMethod(Class,Object,Object[],int)

getMethod

java.lang.reflect.Method getMethod(java.lang.String methodName)
Returns the method reflection object with the specified method name and container class and parameter types defined in this signature.

If there is no Java method with this name, class and parameters or return type is different, an exception is thrown.

Parameters:
methodName - the method name to find.
Returns:
the java.lang.reflect.Method object found.

decInstanceMethod

TypeNativeInstanceMethod decInstanceMethod(java.lang.Class methodClass)
Declares a native instance method type using the specified native method class and this signature.

Current implementation is:

return getTypeManager().decInstanceMethod(methodClass,this);

Parameters:
methodClass - the native method class or interface to use.
Returns:
the native type of the declaration.
See Also:
NativeTypeManager.decInstanceMethod(Class,NativeInstanceMethodSignature), NativeBehaviorSignature.decBehavior(Class)

newInstanceMethodReflection

NativeInstanceMethodReflection newInstanceMethodReflection(java.lang.String methodName)
Creates a native instance method reflection wrapper using this signature and the specified method name.

It is implemented calling NativeBehaviorSignature.newBehaviorReflection(Member) with the method returned by getMethod(String) using the specified method name.

Parameters:
methodName - the method name to find.
Returns:
a new NativeInstanceMethodReflection object as a callback of the specified method.

newDirectInstanceMethodCallback

NativeDirectInstanceMethodCallback newDirectInstanceMethodCallback(java.lang.String methodName)
Creates a new direct instance method callback of the Java method using this signature and the specified method name.

It is implemented calling NativeBehaviorSignature.newDirectCallback(Member) with the method returned by getMethod(String) using the specified method name.

Parameters:
methodName - the method name to find.
Returns:
a new NativeDirectInstanceMethodCallback as a callback of the specified method.
